Manual chamber data post-processing notes: initial QAQC plots using metadata incubation start/end times indicate that the incubation period was only 15 mins instead 75 mins for both miniDOT (SNs 412314 and 255981; one miniDOT was swept away). Upon review of the data; photos; etc.; we determined that the incubation end time was probably manually recorded in DST as opposed to PST. We added 60 mins to the incubation period and replotted the data; which showed that there was 75 mins of data. SGF edited the metadata fields "Manual_Chamber_Incubation_End_Time_PST" and Manual_Chamber_Time_Turned_Off_PST" to add 60 mins;  changing the times from 15:08 to 16:08 to reflect the actual data.
